**Answer:** Manusmriti 11.131 prescribes that for killing a cat (alongside a mongoose, blue jay, frog, dog, iguana, owl, or crow), one should perform **the vow for the slaying of a Shudra** — which per 11.130 means either six months of penance, or giving eleven white cows and one bull to a Brahmana.

Note: In the corpus, this content appears in corpus chapter 12 (the corpus chapter numbering doesn't align 1:1 with traditional Manusmriti chapter numbering — corpus chapter 11 covers only 6 verses on gifts, while corpus chapter 12 contains the bulk of traditional Manusmriti chapter 11 including the expiation rules).
